The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control confirmed four new cases of coronavirus (COVID-19) in the country, bringing the total to 26 so far. Meanwhile, of the 26 confirmed cases, 2 have been discharged with no death. A tweet by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) via its official Twitter handle: @ncdcgov on Sunday morning, disclosed that the total number of confirmed cases is now 26, noting that two has fully recovered and have been discharged while no death has been recorded. One new case of #COVID19 has been confirmed in Oyo state, Nigeria As at 08:05 am on the 22nd of March, there are 26 confirmed cases of #COVID19 in Nigeria Of the 26 confirmed cases, 2 have been discharged with no death pic.twitter.com/Usk6KoKgOy — NCDC (@NCDCgov) March 22, 2020  Currently; Lagos – 19 FCT – 3 Ogun – 2 Ekiti – 1 Oyo – 1 Total: 26 confirmed cases